LAFS implementation log
Date: 2026-03-23
Workspace: C:\Users\AI\lunaos

Summary
- Added LunaOS DATA space (ID 2) implementing the first lafs object store.
- Added TEST space for create/write/read/list/persistence verification.
- Extended SECURITY capability issuance for DATA read/mutate/list domains.
- Extended BOOT to start SECURITY, DATA, and TEST in sequence.
- Reworked image layout and manifest to embed BOOT, SECURITY, DATA, TEST, and lafs store metadata.

Design
- Storage model:
  - lafs is a capability-gated object store, not a POSIX/FAT-like namespace.
  - Objects live in a fixed-slot object library.
  - Maximum objects: 128
  - Slot size: 512 KiB per object
  - Total object payload capacity: 64 MiB
- Disk layout:
  - Backing disk is the same raw QEMU boot disk.
  - lafs starts at LBA 2048.
  - Sector 2048: superblock
  - Next 32 sectors: object record table (128 records x 128 bytes)
  - Remaining sectors: object slot payloads
- Metadata:
  - object id: 128-bit Luna object id (`low`, `high`)
  - object type
  - flags
  - encryption_flags placeholder
  - created_at / modified_at
  - content size
  - slot index
- IPC model:
  - SECURITY gate remains at 0x31000
  - DATA gate at 0x32000
  - DATA payload buffer at 0x33000
  - object id list buffer at 0x37000
- Capability model:
  - `LUNA_CAP_DATA_OBJECT_READ` -> read token
  - `LUNA_CAP_DATA_OBJECT_MUTATE` -> create/write/delete token
  - `LUNA_CAP_DATA_OBJECT_LIST` -> list token
  - DATA validates CID values on every operation

Implemented interfaces
- `create_object(cap_token, metadata) -> object_id`
- `write_object(cap_token, object_id, offset, data) -> status`
- `read_object(cap_token, object_id, offset, size) -> data`
- `delete_object(cap_token, object_id) -> status`
- `list_objects(cap_token) -> [object_id]`

